{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I want to talk to you today a little bit"},{"time":3000,"text":"about predictable irrationality."},{"time":6000,"text":"And my interest in irrational behavior"},{"time":10000,"text":"started many years ago in the hospital."},{"time":13000,"text":"I was burned very badly."},{"time":17000,"text":"And if you spend a lot of time in hospital,"},{"time":20000,"text":"you'll see a lot of types of irrationalities."},{"time":23000,"text":"And the one that particularly bothered me in the burn department"},{"time":28000,"text":"was the process by which the nurses took the bandage off me."},{"time":33000,"text":"Now, you must have all taken a Band-Aid off at some point,"},{"time":35000,"text":"and you must have wondered what's the right approach."},{"time":38000,"text":"Do you rip it off quickly -- short duration but high intensity --"},{"time":42000,"text":"or do you take your Band-Aid off slowly --"},{"time":44000,"text":"you take a long time, but each second is not as painful --"},{"time":48000,"text":"which one of those is the right approach?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"The nurses in my department thought that the right approach"},{"time":55000,"text":"was the ripping one, so they would grab hold and they would rip,"},{"time":58000,"text":"and they would grab hold and they would rip."},{"time":60000,"text":"And because I had 70 percent of my body burned, it would take about an hour."},{"time":64000,"text":"And as you can imagine,"},{"time":67000,"text":"I hated that moment of ripping with incredible intensity."},{"time":71000,"text":"And I would try to reason with them and say,"},{"time":73000,"text":"\"Why don't we try something else?"},{"time":74000,"text":"Why don't we take it a little longer --"},{"time":76000,"text":"maybe two hours instead of an hour -- and have less of this intensity?\""},{"time":81000,"text":"And the nurses told me two things."},{"time":83000,"text":"They told me that they had the right model of the patient --"},{"time":87000,"text":"that they knew what was the right thing to do to minimize my pain --"},{"time":90000,"text":"and they also told me that the word patient doesn't mean"},{"time":93000,"text":"to make suggestions or to interfere or ..."},{"time":95000,"text":"This is not just in Hebrew, by the way."},{"time":98000,"text":"It's in every language I've had experience with so far."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101000,"text":"And, you know, there's not much -- there wasn't much I could do,"},{"time":105000,"text":"and they kept on doing what they were doing."},{"time":108000,"text":"And about three years later, when I left the hospital,"},{"time":110000,"text":"I started studying at the university."},{"time":113000,"text":"And one of the most interesting lessons I learned"},{"time":116000,"text":"was that there is an experimental method"},{"time":118000,"text":"that if you have a question you can create a replica of this question"},{"time":122000,"text":"in some abstract way, and you can try to examine this question,"},{"time":126000,"text":"maybe learn something about the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128000,"text":"So that's what I did."},{"time":130000,"text":"I was still interested"},{"time":131000,"text":"in this question of how do you take bandages off burn patients."},{"time":133000,"text":"So originally I didn't have much money,"},{"time":136000,"text":"so I went to a hardware store and I bought a carpenter's vice."},{"time":140000,"text":"And I would bring people to the lab and I would put their finger in it,"},{"time":144000,"text":"and I would crunch it a little bit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":148000,"text":"And I would crunch it for long periods and short periods,"},{"time":151000,"text":"and pain that went up and pain that went down,"},{"time":153000,"text":"and with breaks and without breaks -- all kinds of versions of pain."},{"time":157000,"text":"And when I finished hurting people a little bit, I would ask them,"},{"time":159000,"text":"so, how painful was this? Or, how painful was this?"},{"time":161000,"text":"Or, if you had to choose between the last two,"},{"time":163000,"text":"which one would you choose?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":165000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":168000,"text":"I kept on doing this for a while."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":173000,"text":"And then, like all good academic projects, I got more funding."},{"time":177000,"text":"I moved to sounds, electrical shocks --"},{"time":179000,"text":"I even had a pain suit that I could get people to feel much more pain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184000,"text":"But at the end of this process,"},{"time":188000,"text":"what I learned was that the nurses were wrong."},{"time":191000,"text":"Here were wonderful people with good intentions"},{"time":194000,"text":"and plenty of experience, and nevertheless"},{"time":196000,"text":"they were getting things wrong predictably all the time."},{"time":200000,"text":"It turns out that because we don't encode duration"},{"time":203000,"text":"in the way that we encode intensity,"},{"time":205000,"text":"I would have had less pain if the duration would have been longer"},{"time":209000,"text":"and the intensity was lower."},{"time":211000,"text":"It turns out it would have been better to start with my face,"},{"time":214000,"text":"which was much more painful, and move toward my legs,"},{"time":216000,"text":"giving me a trend of improvement over time --"},{"time":219000,"text":"that would have been also less painful."},{"time":220000,"text":"And it also turns out that it would have been good"},{"time":222000,"text":"to give me breaks in the middle to kind of recuperate from the pain."},{"time":224000,"text":"All of these would have been great things to do,"},{"time":226000,"text":"and my nurses had no idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229000,"text":"And from that point on I started thinking,"},{"time":230000,"text":"are the nurses the only people in the world who get things wrong"},{"time":233000,"text":"in this particular decision, or is it a more general case?"},{"time":236000,"text":"And it turns out it's a more general case --"},{"time":238000,"text":"there's a lot of mistakes we do."},{"time":241000,"text":"And I want to give you one example of one of these irrationalities,"},{"time":246000,"text":"and I want to talk to you about cheating."},{"time":249000,"text":"And the reason I picked cheating is because it's interesting,"},{"time":251000,"text":"but also it tells us something, I think,"},{"time":253000,"text":"about the stock market situation we're in."},{"time":256000,"text":"So, my interest in cheating started"},{"time":259000,"text":"when Enron came on the scene, exploded all of a sudden,"},{"time":261000,"text":"and I started thinking about what is happening here."},{"time":264000,"text":"Is it the case that there was kind of"},{"time":265000,"text":"a few apples who are capable of doing these things,"},{"time":268000,"text":"or are we talking a more endemic situation,"},{"time":270000,"text":"that many people are actually capable of behaving this way?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":274000,"text":"So, like we usually do, I decided to do a simple experiment."},{"time":278000,"text":"And here's how it went."},{"time":279000,"text":"If you were in the experiment, I would pass you a sheet of paper"},{"time":282000,"text":"with 20 simple math problems that everybody could solve,"},{"time":286000,"text":"but I wouldn't give you enough time."},{"time":288000,"text":"When the five minutes were over, I would say,"},{"time":290000,"text":"\"Pass me the sheets of paper, and I'll pay you a dollar per question.\""},{"time":293000,"text":"People did this. I would pay people four dollars for their task --"},{"time":297000,"text":"on average people would solve four problems."},{"time":299000,"text":"Other people I would tempt to cheat."},{"time":302000,"text":"I would pass their sheet of paper."},{"time":303000,"text":"When the five minutes were over, I would say,"},{"time":305000,"text":"\"Please shred the piece of paper."},{"time":306000,"text":"Put the little pieces in your pocket or in your backpack,"},{"time":309000,"text":"and tell me how many questions you got correctly.\""},{"time":312000,"text":"People now solved seven questions on average."},{"time":315000,"text":"Now, it wasn't as if there was a few bad apples --"},{"time":320000,"text":"a few people cheated a lot."},{"time":323000,"text":"Instead, what we saw is a lot of people who cheat a little bit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326000,"text":"Now, in economic theory,"},{"time":329000,"text":"cheating is a very simple cost-benefit analysis."},{"time":332000,"text":"You say, what's the probability of being caught?"},{"time":334000,"text":"How much do I stand to gain from cheating?"},{"time":337000,"text":"And how much punishment would I get if I get caught?"},{"time":339000,"text":"And you weigh these options out --"},{"time":341000,"text":"you do the simple cost-benefit analysis,"},{"time":343000,"text":"and you decide whether it's worthwhile to commit the crime or not."},{"time":346000,"text":"So, we try to test this."},{"time":348000,"text":"For some people, we varied how much money they could get away with --"},{"time":352000,"text":"how much money they could steal."},{"time":353000,"text":"We paid them 10 cents per correct question, 50 cents,"},{"time":356000,"text":"a dollar, five dollars, 10 dollars per correct question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359000,"text":"You would expect that as the amount of money on the table increases,"},{"time":363000,"text":"people would cheat more, but in fact it wasn't the case."},{"time":366000,"text":"We got a lot of people cheating by stealing by a little bit."},{"time":369000,"text":"What about the probability of being caught?"},{"time":372000,"text":"Some people shredded half the sheet of paper,"},{"time":374000,"text":"so there was some evidence left."},{"time":375000,"text":"Some people shredded the whole sheet of paper."},{"time":377000,"text":"Some people shredded everything, went out of the room,"},{"time":380000,"text":"and paid themselves from the bowl of money that had over 100 dollars."},{"time":383000,"text":"You would expect that as the probability of being caught goes down,"},{"time":386000,"text":"people would cheat more, but again, this was not the case."},{"time":389000,"text":"Again, a lot of people cheated by just by a little bit,"},{"time":392000,"text":"and they were insensitive to these economic incentives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395000,"text":"So we said, \"If people are not sensitive"},{"time":396000,"text":"to the economic rational theory explanations, to these forces,"},{"time":401000,"text":"what could be going on?\""},{"time":404000,"text":"And we thought maybe what is happening is that there are two forces."},{"time":407000,"text":"At one hand, we all want to look at ourselves in the mirror"},{"time":409000,"text":"and feel good about ourselves, so we don't want to cheat."},{"time":412000,"text":"On the other hand, we can cheat a little bit,"},{"time":414000,"text":"and still feel good about ourselves."},{"time":416000,"text":"So, maybe what is happening is that"},{"time":417000,"text":"there's a level of cheating we can't go over,"},{"time":419000,"text":"but we can still benefit from cheating at a low degree,"},{"time":423000,"text":"as long as it doesn't change our impressions about ourselves."},{"time":426000,"text":"We call this like a personal fudge factor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430000,"text":"Now, how would you test a personal fudge factor?"},{"time":434000,"text":"Initially we said, what can we do to shrink the fudge factor?"},{"time":438000,"text":"So, we got people to the lab, and we said,"},{"time":440000,"text":"\"We have two tasks for you today.\""},{"time":442000,"text":"First, we asked half the people"},{"time":443000,"text":"to recall either 10 books they read in high school,"},{"time":445000,"text":"or to recall The Ten Commandments,"},{"time":448000,"text":"and then we tempted them with cheating."},{"time":450000,"text":"Turns out the people who tried to recall The Ten Commandments --"},{"time":453000,"text":"and in our sample nobody could recall all of The Ten Commandments --"},{"time":456000,"text":"but those people who tried to recall The Ten Commandments,"},{"time":460000,"text":"given the opportunity to cheat, did not cheat at all."},{"time":463000,"text":"It wasn't that the more religious people --"},{"time":465000,"text":"the people who remembered more of the Commandments -- cheated less,"},{"time":466000,"text":"and the less religious people --"},{"time":468000,"text":"the people who couldn't remember almost any Commandments --"},{"time":469000,"text":"cheated more."},{"time":471000,"text":"The moment people thought about trying to recall The Ten Commandments,"},{"time":475000,"text":"they stopped cheating."},{"time":476000,"text":"In fact, even when we gave self-declared atheists"},{"time":478000,"text":"the task of swearing on the Bible and we give them a chance to cheat,"},{"time":482000,"text":"they don't cheat at all."},{"time":486000,"text":"Now, Ten Commandments is something that is hard"},{"time":488000,"text":"to bring into the education system, so we said,"},{"time":490000,"text":"\"Why don't we get people to sign the honor code?\""},{"time":492000,"text":"So, we got people to sign,"},{"time":494000,"text":"\"I understand that this short survey falls under the MIT Honor Code.\""},{"time":498000,"text":"Then they shredded it. No cheating whatsoever."},{"time":501000,"text":"And this is particularly interesting,"},{"time":502000,"text":"because MIT doesn't have an honor code."},{"time":504000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":509000,"text":"So, all this was about decreasing the fudge factor."},{"time":513000,"text":"What about increasing the fudge factor?"},{"time":516000,"text":"The first experiment -- I walked around MIT"},{"time":518000,"text":"and I distributed six-packs of Cokes in the refrigerators --"},{"time":521000,"text":"these were common refrigerators for the undergrads."},{"time":523000,"text":"And I came back to measure what we technically call"},{"time":526000,"text":"the half-lifetime of Coke -- how long does it last in the refrigerators?"},{"time":530000,"text":"As you can expect it doesn't last very long; people take it."},{"time":533000,"text":"In contrast, I took a plate with six one-dollar bills,"},{"time":537000,"text":"and I left those plates in the same refrigerators."},{"time":540000,"text":"No bill ever disappeared."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541000,"text":"Now, this is not a good social science experiment,"},{"time":544000,"text":"so to do it better I did the same experiment"},{"time":547000,"text":"as I described to you before."},{"time":549000,"text":"A third of the people we passed the sheet, they gave it back to us."},{"time":552000,"text":"A third of the people we passed it to, they shredded it,"},{"time":555000,"text":"they came to us and said,"},{"time":556000,"text":"\"Mr. Experimenter, I solved X problems. Give me X dollars.\""},{"time":559000,"text":"A third of the people, when they finished shredding the piece of paper,"},{"time":562000,"text":"they came to us and said,"},{"time":564000,"text":"\"Mr Experimenter, I solved X problems. Give me X tokens.\""},{"time":570000,"text":"We did not pay them with dollars; we paid them with something else."},{"time":573000,"text":"And then they took the something else, they walked 12 feet to the side,"},{"time":576000,"text":"and exchanged it for dollars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578000,"text":"Think about the following intuition."},{"time":580000,"text":"How bad would you feel about taking a pencil from work home,"},{"time":583000,"text":"compared to how bad would you feel"},{"time":585000,"text":"about taking 10 cents from a petty cash box?"},{"time":587000,"text":"These things feel very differently."},{"time":590000,"text":"Would being a step removed from cash for a few seconds"},{"time":593000,"text":"by being paid by token make a difference?"},{"time":596000,"text":"Our subjects doubled their cheating."},{"time":598000,"text":"I'll tell you what I think"},{"time":600000,"text":"about this and the stock market in a minute."},{"time":603000,"text":"But this did not solve the big problem I had with Enron yet,"},{"time":607000,"text":"because in Enron, there's also a social element."},{"time":610000,"text":"People see each other behaving."},{"time":611000,"text":"In fact, every day when we open the news"},{"time":613000,"text":"we see examples of people cheating."},{"time":615000,"text":"What does this cause us?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":618000,"text":"So, we did another experiment."},{"time":619000,"text":"We got a big group of students to be in the experiment,"},{"time":622000,"text":"and we prepaid them."},{"time":623000,"text":"So everybody got an envelope with all the money for the experiment,"},{"time":626000,"text":"and we told them that at the end, we asked them"},{"time":628000,"text":"to pay us back the money they didn't make. OK?"},{"time":632000,"text":"The same thing happens."},{"time":633000,"text":"When we give people the opportunity to cheat, they cheat."},{"time":635000,"text":"They cheat just by a little bit, all the same."},{"time":638000,"text":"But in this experiment we also hired an acting student."},{"time":641000,"text":"This acting student stood up after 30 seconds, and said,"},{"time":645000,"text":"\"I solved everything. What do I do now?\""},{"time":648000,"text":"And the experimenter said, \"If you've finished everything, go home."},{"time":652000,"text":"That's it. The task is finished.\""},{"time":653000,"text":"So, now we had a student -- an acting student --"},{"time":657000,"text":"that was a part of the group."},{"time":659000,"text":"Nobody knew it was an actor."},{"time":661000,"text":"And they clearly cheated in a very, very serious way."},{"time":665000,"text":"What would happen to the other people in the group?"},{"time":668000,"text":"Will they cheat more, or will they cheat less?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":671000,"text":"Here is what happens."},{"time":673000,"text":"It turns out it depends on what kind of sweatshirt they're wearing."},{"time":677000,"text":"Here is the thing."},{"time":679000,"text":"We ran this at Carnegie Mellon and Pittsburgh."},{"time":682000,"text":"And at Pittsburgh there are two big universities,"},{"time":684000,"text":"Carnegie Mellon and University of Pittsburgh."},{"time":687000,"text":"All of the subjects sitting in the experiment"},{"time":689000,"text":"were Carnegie Mellon students."},{"time":691000,"text":"When the actor who was getting up was a Carnegie Mellon student --"},{"time":695000,"text":"he was actually a Carnegie Mellon student --"},{"time":697000,"text":"but he was a part of their group, cheating went up."},{"time":701000,"text":"But when he actually had a University of Pittsburgh sweatshirt,"},{"time":705000,"text":"cheating went down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":710000,"text":"Now, this is important, because remember,"},{"time":713000,"text":"when the moment the student stood up,"},{"time":715000,"text":"it made it clear to everybody that they could get away with cheating,"},{"time":718000,"text":"because the experimenter said,"},{"time":720000,"text":"\"You've finished everything. Go home,\" and they went with the money."},{"time":722000,"text":"So it wasn't so much about the probability of being caught again."},{"time":725000,"text":"It was about the norms for cheating."},{"time":728000,"text":"If somebody from our in-group cheats and we see them cheating,"},{"time":731000,"text":"we feel it's more appropriate, as a group, to behave this way."},{"time":735000,"text":"But if it's somebody from another group, these terrible people --"},{"time":737000,"text":"I mean, not terrible in this --"},{"time":739000,"text":"but somebody we don't want to associate ourselves with,"},{"time":741000,"text":"from another university, another group,"},{"time":743000,"text":"all of a sudden people's awareness of honesty goes up --"},{"time":746000,"text":"a little bit like The Ten Commandments experiment --"},{"time":748000,"text":"and people cheat even less."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752000,"text":"So, what have we learned from this about cheating?"},{"time":756000,"text":"We've learned that a lot of people can cheat."},{"time":759000,"text":"They cheat just by a little bit."},{"time":762000,"text":"When we remind people about their morality, they cheat less."},{"time":766000,"text":"When we get bigger distance from cheating,"},{"time":769000,"text":"from the object of money, for example, people cheat more."},{"time":773000,"text":"And when we see cheating around us,"},{"time":775000,"text":"particularly if it's a part of our in-group, cheating goes up."},{"time":779000,"text":"Now, if we think about this in terms of the stock market,"},{"time":782000,"text":"think about what happens."},{"time":783000,"text":"What happens in a situation when you create something"},{"time":786000,"text":"where you pay people a lot of money"},{"time":788000,"text":"to see reality in a slightly distorted way?"},{"time":791000,"text":"Would they not be able to see it this way?"},{"time":794000,"text":"Of course they would."},{"time":795000,"text":"What happens when you do other things,"},{"time":796000,"text":"like you remove things from money?"},{"time":798000,"text":"You call them stock, or stock options, derivatives,"},{"time":801000,"text":"mortgage-backed securities."},{"time":802000,"text":"Could it be that with those more distant things,"},{"time":805000,"text":"it's not a token for one second,"},{"time":807000,"text":"it's something that is many steps removed from money"},{"time":809000,"text":"for a much longer time -- could it be that people will cheat even more?"},{"time":813000,"text":"And what happens to the social environment"},{"time":815000,"text":"when people see other people behave around them?"},{"time":818000,"text":"I think all of those forces worked in a very bad way"},{"time":822000,"text":"in the stock market."}]},{"cues":[{"time":824000,"text":"More generally, I want to tell you something"},{"time":827000,"text":"about behavioral economics."},{"time":830000,"text":"We have many intuitions in our life,"},{"time":834000,"text":"and the point is that many of these intuitions are wrong."},{"time":837000,"text":"The question is, are we going to test those intuitions?"},{"time":840000,"text":"We can think about how we're going to test this intuition"},{"time":842000,"text":"in our private life, in our business life,"},{"time":844000,"text":"and most particularly when it goes to policy,"},{"time":847000,"text":"when we think about things like No Child Left Behind,"},{"time":850000,"text":"when you create new stock markets, when you create other policies --"},{"time":853000,"text":"taxation, health care and so on."},{"time":856000,"text":"And the difficulty of testing our intuition"},{"time":858000,"text":"was the big lesson I learned"},{"time":860000,"text":"when I went back to the nurses to talk to them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":862000,"text":"So I went back to talk to them"},{"time":864000,"text":"and tell them what I found out about removing bandages."},{"time":867000,"text":"And I learned two interesting things."},{"time":869000,"text":"One was that my favorite nurse, Ettie,"},{"time":871000,"text":"told me that I did not take her pain into consideration."},{"time":875000,"text":"She said, \"Of course, you know, it was very painful for you."},{"time":877000,"text":"But think about me as a nurse,"},{"time":879000,"text":"taking, removing the bandages of somebody I liked,"},{"time":881000,"text":"and had to do it repeatedly over a long period of time."},{"time":884000,"text":"Creating so much torture was not something that was good for me, too.\""},{"time":887000,"text":"And she said maybe part of the reason was it was difficult for her."},{"time":892000,"text":"But it was actually more interesting than that, because she said,"},{"time":895000,"text":"\"I did not think that your intuition was right."},{"time":900000,"text":"I felt my intuition was correct.\""},{"time":901000,"text":"So, if you think about all of your intuitions,"},{"time":903000,"text":"it's very hard to believe that your intuition is wrong."},{"time":907000,"text":"And she said, \"Given the fact that I thought my intuition was right ...\" --"},{"time":910000,"text":"she thought her intuition was right --"},{"time":912000,"text":"it was very difficult for her to accept doing a difficult experiment"},{"time":917000,"text":"to try and check whether she was wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":919000,"text":"But in fact, this is the situation we're all in all the time."},{"time":923000,"text":"We have very strong intuitions about all kinds of things --"},{"time":926000,"text":"our own ability, how the economy works,"},{"time":929000,"text":"how we should pay school teachers."},{"time":931000,"text":"But unless we start testing those intuitions,"},{"time":934000,"text":"we're not going to do better."},{"time":936000,"text":"And just think about how better my life would have been"},{"time":938000,"text":"if these nurses would have been willing to check their intuition,"},{"time":940000,"text":"and how everything would have been better"},{"time":941000,"text":"if we just start doing more systematic experimentation of our intuitions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":946000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}